I have to first apologize because I do not recall the names of the people who helped me.  I hosted an alumni Thanksgiving dinner for my former theatre students on Wednesday. We were taking precautions and that included abandoning our traditional potluck style in favour of catering. There was a need for individually packaged meals however (not sharing food spaces/utensils/etc), so instead of the typical catering option, we decided it was best to order a dozen meals. I opted for meals that had the two side options. The order was ready and waiting in a convenient bag when I arrived. I glanced into the bags and saw all meals accounted for and some sides as well. I have never done carry out from Nando’s before, so I just assumed the sides were also inside the boxes of chicken. I got home and guests immediately began arriving. As we unpacked the food, I soon realized we had only 8 sides. By this point, I had a full party and unfortunately, no one but myself was able to drive. I couldn’t leave. I called the restaurant and explained my situation to a young woman (Maria? Cynthia? I don’t recall!) who said they didn’t have another bag that I’d missed but would make the sides fresh. When I explained I couldn’t leave, she then offered to find someone who could drive it over. Within forty minutes, a gentleman had dropped off 16 missing sides, all freshly made and ready to be consumed. He even called as a follow up to ensure I had picked them up (I live in a building that asks food deliveries to be left with the concierge for pick up). It was the easiest “oops” moment I’ve ever encountered and I cannot say enough about the support and patient and helpful customer service received from this location. There was no moment of “what now?” or trying to cut down on portions to ensure everyone had enough to eat. I am so truly grateful to both the person who took my call and the gentleman who left to drive them to us in time for our traditional thanksgiving dinner. Thank you!!!

Not exactly what I was expecting when we first walked in, but after understanding the concept a bit more it was actually really good. You are seated and told what your table number is.  You then order and pay at the counter. Get glasses for your drinks. Drink station is self serve. Get any extra sauces that you want, and they bring your food to the table. Chicken was juicy, and fell off the bone. Had really good flavor especially with some of the extra sauce on it. Being self serve, table side service is basically non existent, which again fits the concept of the restaurant, but a change of pace of your are looking for a full service sit down restaurant.
